<h1>Next Steps</h1>
<p>After this, you can move onto other methods like Roux or Metha. While learning a new method, don't try and time yourself at the beginning, it will obviously be slower, but as you get better at it you will reach speeds you could never have before.</p>
<p>I find <a href="https://cubingcheatsheet.com/">Dan's Cubing Cheatsheet</a> very useful and you can also download the app. I also recommend <a href="https://www.youtube.com/jperm">JPerm's Youtube Channel</a> for helpful tutorials.</p>
<p>Or you can go and try learning how to solve different cubes like the 2x2, bigger cubes like the 4x4 or different shapes like the pyramix or shapeshifters like the mirror cube or the windmill cube.</p>
<p>There are endless opportunities, it is whether you will take them or not.</p>
<p>That's all from me, your guide. Happy cubing everyone!</p>
